This paper deals with the problem of multi-robot motion planning, which is a core topic in robotics. The use of reinforcement learning and motion constraints suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and the mention of a general approach make it likely to also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The mention of a smooth projection that guarantees collision-free trajectories suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and trajectory planning suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
